modules.description: This module defines a type `t` representing the SameSite attribute values for HTTP cookies, including `default`, `none`, `lax`, and `strict`. It provides equality checking, comparison, S-expression conversion, and cookie string serialization. Concrete use cases include setting and validating SameSite attributes in HTTP cookie headers.

This module parses, constructs, and serializes HTTP cookies according to RFC6265. It handles cookie attributes such as name, value, domain, path, max-age, secure, http-only, same-site, and extension, providing validation and error reporting for each. It supports converting cookies to and from HTTP header formats used in requests and responses.
